    <section id="postingbody">
        <div class="print-information print-qrcode-container">
            <p class="print-qrcode-label">QR Code Link to This Post</p>
            <div class="print-qrcode" data-location="http://anchorage.craigslist.org/fbh/6038792936.html"></div>
        </div>
We are a family-owned and operated tourist business. Our guests come from all over the world to enjoy our little slice of heaven: amazing scenery, bird watching, wildlife, mountains, glaciers, and fishing to start.<br>
<br>
As a summer staff member, we invite you to work hard with us in a team oriented atmosphere. We run everyday/all week and are looking for people to help us take our cafe to the next level. We look for applicants with a good attitude and the ability to learn; excellent customer skills and the ability to cross-sell.  On-the-job training is provided for those with less experience. Staff MUST be able to multi-task as daily duties vary regularly.  Shifts run 7am-3pm and 10am-6pm. A State of Alaska Food Worker Card (<a href="http://dec.state.ak.us/eh/fss/" rel="nofollow">http://dec.state.ak.us/eh/fss/</a>) is required.<br>
<br>
The successful candidate will prepare all breakfast and lunch items on the menu, scoop ice cream, and make espressos. This person will assist with food prep, washing dishes, busing tables, cashiering, unloading supplies, cleaning the cafe each night and housekeeping for the Inn. Housekeeping experience is preferred - cleaning rooms and folding laundry will be a regular assignment. We also plant and maintain a large garden at the cabin. Weeding and watering tasks rotate weekly between staff members. This position is physically demanding, requires attention to detail and an ability to work independently and efficiently. <br>
<br>
Since we are located across the bay, staff members need to be comfortable with long periods away from town/city life. This job requires an independent person who does not mind time alone, with the ability to enjoy the area and self-directed activities. Staff housing is available with no electricity/running water about 5 miles from town.  A coin-op shower and laundry facilities are located at the job site. Lunch is provided at the cafe.  Limited WIFI is available for emails and web searches; however, WIFI cannot be used for downloading movies, Skype, or large data downloads, etc.  Cell phone service is not available if you have AT&T or GCI.  Our current carrier is Verizon which has to be activated in Anchorage. <br>
<br>
During free time, staff members enjoy fishing, hiking, beach combing, berry picking, whale watching, wildlife viewing, and kayaking. There are photo opportunities everywhere! <br>
<br>
Employment for seasonal jobs runs from Memorial Day to Labor Day. Applicants must be available 1 week before opening. Usually around May 15th. <br>
<br>
Applicants must be able and willing to do all jobs in our team-oriented environment. If you are a hard-working, friendly, trustworthy and a reliable person we are interested in you being a part of our team.<br>
<br>
Needed for applying: <br>
1) Resume with current phone number, mailing address and email<br>
2) Three work-related references (with contact numbers) <br>
3) A current photo<br>
4) Applicant must be able to lift up to 50 pounds<br>
<br>
ABSOLUTELY NO PETS / NO DRUGS / SMOKING IS NOT PERMITTED ON PREMISES<br>
    </section>

